<html><p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Micro Focus Hybrid Cloud Management X (HCMX) simplifies the delivery, consumption, and governance of IT services and resources. HCMX is delivered as part of a single converged solution that provides the capabilities of HCMX and Service Management Automation X (SMAX) integrated Configuration Management System (CMS) and Operations Orchestration (OO) solution. HCMX offers the following cloud management capabilities:</span></span></span></p>

<ul>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Design and Deploy (DND)</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Cost governance and resource optimization (CGRO)</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Image aggregation</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">IT process orchestration</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Service portal</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Content store</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Universal CMDB</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">CMS UI</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Mobile application</span></span></span></li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">HCMX CGRO capability enables customers to optimize cloud spending with various cloud providers such as Amazon Web Services (AWS) and Microsoft Azure. HCMX CGRO capability provides the following functionalities:</span></span></span></p>

<ul>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Cost governance: Cost governance reports help visualize public cloud spending. These reports enable you to review your public cloud costs, your cloud activity and your usage of public cloud resources.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Cloud insights: Cloud insights are cost-saving recommendations calculated by HCMX CGRO functionality. Cloud insights help you understand how you might reduce and optimize your cloud spend.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Cloud cost limits: A cloud cost limit allows you to specify a threshold for a cloud spend group, view a spend group's spend compared to the threshold, and receive email notifications when that threshold is exceeded.</span></span></span></li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">This practitioner note describes steps involved in configuring CGRO capability, and using CGRO capability with the following use cases:</span></span></span></p>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Understand public cloud spending.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Identify opportunities for cost savings.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Identify out of compliance spend groups.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">This practitioner note assumes that the&nbsp;<span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">DND and CGRO capabilities were installed during HCMX installation.&nbsp;</span></span></span>If CGRO and/or DND has not been installed, add the DND and CGRO capability to an existing installation of HCMX/SMAX.&nbsp;The CGRO capability can be used in multiple tenants of HCMX/SMAX. CGRO has a pre-requisite of DND installation but it does not require that DND be deployed to a&nbsp;tenant. CGRO can be used with a tenant that does not have DND capability deployed to it.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">This practitioner note has the following sections:</span></span></span></p>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Configure CGRO</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Use CGRO</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<h2>Configure CGRO</h2>

<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The Configuration of CGRO creates the necessary foundation for using CGRO functionalities and it includes the following steps:</span></span></span></p>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Derive agent interface URL</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Configure application settings</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Verify that CGRO menu options are visible</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Configure authorization for CGRO</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<h3>Derive agent interface URL</h3>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Log on to the suite administration portal as user <b>suite-admin</b> at the following URL: <span class="MsoHyperlink" style="color:#0563c1"><span style="text-decoration:underline">https://&lt;HCMX-Server-FQDN&gt;/bo</span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span class="MsoHyperlink" style="color:#0563c1"><span style="text-decoration:underline"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/c/c9/01-CGRO-SuiteLogin.PNG" height="572" hspace="0" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/c/c9/01-CGRO-SuiteLogin.PNG" style="width:716px;height:572px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="716"></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 11px; margin-left: 8px;"></p>

<ol start="2">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the <b>suite administration</b> home page, navigate to <b>TENANTS</b>. A list of tenants is displayed.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/c/cf/CGRO-BOHomePage.PNG" height="295" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_6036cce7ab5d53.38899721.png" style="width: 800px; height: 295px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></span></span></span></p>

<ol start="3">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the list of tenants, click the <strong>number</strong> under the ID column for the tenant in which you would like to use CGRO functionality.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/6/69/CGRO-TenantList-1.PNG" height="213" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_6036cdcd18d3f8.12906430.png" style="width: 800px; height: 213px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></span></span></span></p>

<ol start="4">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Note down the tenant<strong> ID and</strong>&nbsp;<strong>URL</strong>&nbsp;field values. Each tenant exposes two portals: Tenant end user portal and Tenant agent interface portal. The tenant end user portal is the portal where the users submit support requests and request for services. The tenant agent interface portal is the portal which allows administrators to configure HCMX, agents to fullfil requests submitted by the end users, etc. The URL field contains URL to the tenant end user portal. The tenant agent interface URL is required for configuration and usage of CGRO.&nbsp;Construct the tenant agent interface URL as follows: <a>https://HCMXFullyQualifiedDomainName/saw?TENANTID=&lt;Replace with tenant ID value shown on general page&gt;<replace general="" id="" on="" page="" shown="" tenant="" value="" with="">.</replace></a> Bookmark agent interface URL. Click the number in the <strong>Tenant admin</strong> field on the <strong>General</strong> page.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p><br>
<img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/3/39/CGRO-TenantGeneral.PNG" height="550" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_603943fccb5446.12244108.png" style="width: 800px; height: 550px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></p>

<ol start="5">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the tenant admin&nbsp;user account <strong>General&nbsp;</strong>page, note down the login name for tenant admin in the <strong>Login name</strong> field. Work with your HCMX administrators to get password for the tenant admin user account if you did not create the tenant. If you had created the tenant, then you would already know password for the tenant admin account.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/7/75/CGRO-TenantAdminUser.PNG" height="510" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395927e514b4.05038001.png" style="width: 800px; height: 510px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></span></span></span></p>

<ol start="6">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the top right corner, click <b>suite admin user’s</b> drop down. Click <b>Logout</b>.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/8/8c/CGRO-BOLogout.PNG" height="601" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_603945d5a19475.67022222.png" style="width: 800px; height: 601px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></span></span></span></p>

<h3>Configure application settings</h3>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Log on to the tenant agent interface&nbsp;as <b>tenant admin</b> user. The tenant agent interface URL was derived in earlier steps.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<ol start="2">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Tenant dashboard is displayed. The dashboard is the default homepage for every user, but it is configurable and can be changed.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/b/bb/CGRO-DashboardHomepage.PNG" height="427" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395a97015bd1.23330465.png" style="width: 800px; height: 427px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></p>

<ol start="3">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">From the <b>mega menu</b> (<b>Three horizontal lines</b> icon), navigate to <b>Administration</b> -&gt; <b>Configuration</b> -&gt; <b>Application Settings</b></span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4e/CGRO-MegaAdminAppSettings.PNG" height="324" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395b3f0d17a0.34259267.png" style="width: 800px; height: 324px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></p>

<ol start="4">
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In the <b>APPLICATION SETTINGS</b> screen, turn on the <b>Enable Cost Governance and Resource Optimization</b> setting.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/7/71/CGRO-AppSettingsCGRO.PNG" height="764" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395c797680c1.60199996.png" style="width: 800px; height: 764px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Scroll to the top of the <b>APPLICATION SETTINGS</b> screen. In the <strong>Tenant key chain</strong>&nbsp;section, if <strong>Create Key Chain</strong> option is still available, click&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Create Key Chain.&nbsp;</strong>In the <strong>Create tenant key chain</strong>&nbsp;window, type in and confirm the passcode. Click <strong>OK</strong>. A tenant key chain is required to support encrypted fields in the tenant.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/a/a7/CGRO-CreateTenantKeyChain.png" height="298" hspace="0" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/a/a7/CGRO-CreateTenantKeyChain.png" style="width:624px;height:298px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="624"></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Scroll to the top of the <b>APPLICATION SETTINGS</b> screen. </span></span></span>&nbsp;Click <strong>Save.</strong></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><strong><img alt="" border="0" file="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4e/CGRO-AppSettingsSave.PNG" height="511" hspace="0" src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_60395ea2032d32.09702179.png" style="width: 800px; height: 511px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;" vspace="0" width="800"></strong></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"></p>
